The defendant Cary O Stallworth was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Possession of THC (2nd+ Offense), a class I felony, Wisconsin Statutes 961.41(3g)(e).
  • Bail Jumping-Misdemeanor, a class A misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 946.49(1)(a).

Per Order of Presiding Judge, Felony Division, this request/motion is hereby assigned to Carolina Stark, Branch 17, for review. jbs
Defendant's pro se request for Huber privileges and/or house arrest received in cases 14CF1779 and 14CM708.  Filed in 14CF1779.

Defendant Cary O Stallworth in court with attorney Paul J. Manley.  Danielle E. Chojnacki appeared for the State of Wisconsin.
Case scheduled for Final Pretrial. Case proceeds to Plea and Sentencing. 
AS TO COUNT  1 and 2: 
The defendant was advised of his constitutional rights and maximum penalties, waived all rights, plead GUILTY and was examined as to the plea.  Plea Questionnaire/Waiver of Rights, Jury Instructions and Addendum to Plea Questionnaire and Waiver of Rights received and filed.  The parties stipulate to the complaint as a factual basis for the plea.  The Court found the defendant guilty and ordered entry of Judgment of Conviction.
Sentencing proceeded.  Statements by the State, defense and defendant.  
AS TO COUNT 1:
Defendant sentenced to serve 9 months in the House of Correction, with release to the Day Reporting Center only, concurrent to COUNT 2 and to case 14CM708, consecutive to any other sentence, with credit for 3 days time served.  Court notes a strong objection to electronic monitoring. COURT STAYED THE SENTENCE and placed the defendant on probation with the State of Wisconsin, Department of Corrections for a period of 18 months. 
AS TO COUNT 2: 
Defendant sentenced to serve 9 months in the House of Correction, with release to the Day Reporting Center only, concurrent to COUNT 1 to case 14CM708, consecutive to any other sentence, with credit for 3 days time served.  Court notes a strong objection to electronic monitoring. COURT STAYED THE SENTENCE and placed the defendant on probation with the State of Wisconsin, Department of Corrections for a period of 18 months. 
CONDITIONS OF PROBATION:
- Maintain Absolute Sobriety, no alcohol.
- No use or possession of controlled substances without a valid 
  prescription taken in the manner and fashion as prescribed.
- Defendant to participate in Alcohol and Drug Assessment
  and successfully complete recommended treatment
  including drug and alcohol testing. 
- No possession of any marijuana. 
- No use of any drug without a valid prescription. 
- No possession of any drug paraphernalia including drug paraphernalia for personal use, manufacturing, delivering or distributing. 
- Complete a Parenting Class. 
- As to COUNT 1 and 2 Court orders court costs, fees, assessments and surcharges, including the DNA surcharge to paid through collection of the probation agent. Any cash bail to apply.  Any remaining balance upon release of probation shall be due immediately; failure to pay will result in an entry of civil judgment.
- Maintain full time work and/or school.
- No possession of any firearm or ammunition. 
- Provide DNA sample, if not already done. 

Appellate rights notice given to the defendant.
